No, now is the part
when I tell you exactly
what you're going to do next.

03:23.537 --> 03:26.324
Start classes
at Costa Verde Community.

03:26.415 --> 03:30.658
You're already enrolled.
History, English Lit.,
Spanish.

03:31.462 --> 03:32.872
And come Monday morning,

03:32.963 --> 03:35.625
you better be parked
in that front row with
a sharp number 2 pencil,

03:35.716 --> 03:38.332
or there is going
to be hell to pay.

03:48.479 --> 03:49.810
(DOOR CLOSING)

03:49.897 --> 03:52.013
(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

04:08.541 --> 04:14.377
Wires are up, accounts
are frozen, we have traffic
cam feeds from all 50 states.

04:14.463 --> 04:16.624
The Patriot Act gives us
a lot of leeway here.

04:16.715 --> 04:18.125
What's our status
on the Bennet girl?

04:18.217 --> 04:20.879
Eyes only. We look,
but we don't touch.

04:21.762 --> 04:26.222
Senator Petrelli has
granted Miss Bennet
a probation for now.

04:26.725 --> 04:28.852
Should the terms
of that arrangement
be compromised,

04:28.936 --> 04:31.928
I will certainly
bring it to his attention,

04:32.231 --> 04:36.645
assuming he finishes
his latte and decides
to show up for work.

04:36.735 --> 04:38.396
Double espresso.

04:41.240 --> 04:43.777
And Claire Bennet
is still off-limits.

04:43.909 --> 04:46.946
Now, I know a lot
of you lost friends
in this crash.

04:47.037 --> 04:49.119
You want payback,
I understand that,

04:49.248 --> 04:51.580
but not all
of these individuals
out there are dangerous.

04:51.667 --> 04:54.079
Some of them
are just plain scared.

04:54.170 --> 04:55.660
And now that they know
they're being pursued,

04:55.754 --> 04:58.166
they're going to be even
that much harder to catch,

04:58.257 --> 05:00.339
which is why
I put in a request to
the White House this morning

05:00.426 --> 05:01.586
to double our funding.

05:01.677 --> 05:05.261
We need to show progress.
These are our targets,
know them.

05:05.347 --> 05:08.635
Hunt them, track them,
and bring them home alive.

05:13.981 --> 05:16.142
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ON RAD/O)

05:16.859 --> 05:18.520
This is so cool.

05:19.570 --> 05:22.482
Road trip.
My mom never
took me anywhere.

05:22.698 --> 05:24.154
Ooh, we should stop
at some skanky diner somewhere

05:24.241 --> 05:27.404
and get some pie
and some milkshakes.

05:27.495 --> 05:28.905
We're not stopping.

05:29.246 --> 05:33.364
Sure? It's a long way
till we get to your dad.

05:37.755 --> 05:39.245
Where is he?

05:40.257 --> 05:42.543
I told you,
just keep heading west.

05:42.635 --> 05:44.421
(TIRES SQUEALING)

05:47.306 --> 05:48.762
(MUSIC STOPS)

05:49.391 --> 05:54.351
Yeah, you told me to keep
heading west. Now I want
to know exactly where he is.

05:54.939 --> 05:56.099
Okay.

05:58.025 --> 06:01.768
He told me that
if he ever had to disappear,
I could find him in Minnesota.

06:01.862 --> 06:05.696
He's got a cabin
in the woods,
about 28 miles west of...

06:05.783 --> 06:07.273
You're lying.

06:09.036 --> 06:11.778
It's amazing how
you can do that.
Tell me where he is.

06:11.872 --> 06:15.865
Okay. He has an ex-wife
who's a flight attendant,
she lives in Des Moines.

06:15.960 --> 06:20.374
They had a kid that
was born with some sort
of weird bone disorder...

06:20.464 --> 06:22.796
Stop! I can tell
when people are lying

06:22.925 --> 06:26.884
because I saw open their
skulls and rip their abilities
out from their brains.

06:26.971 --> 06:28.302
(EXCLAIMS)

06:29.640 --> 06:32.052
So you're like
a serial killer?

06:32.726 --> 06:34.011
(EXHALES)

06:34.103 --> 06:36.139
I'm not a serial killer.

06:38.315 --> 06:41.807
Well, you've got a pattern,
you go after specific victims,
you collect mementos...

06:41.902 --> 06:44.644
Okay, technically,
I'm a serial killer.

06:47.616 --> 06:49.322
Now that we've
established that,
give me one good reason

06:49.410 --> 06:50.900
why I shouldn't tear open
your head right here.

06:50.995 --> 06:53.611
Because you'll never
find your dad.

06:56.500 --> 06:59.492
This is not a road trip.
Do you understand?

06:59.587 --> 07:00.747
(ENGINE STARTING)

07:00.838 --> 07:02.453
(MUSIC RESUMES)

07:19.148 --> 07:20.137
AGENT: Sir.

07:22.526 --> 07:23.936
(BEEPING)

07:26.655 --> 07:28.316
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

07:31.035 --> 07:32.525
Are you Alex?

07:37.041 --> 07:40.124
You're a girl.
Yeah, lam.

07:41.378 --> 07:45.121
It's just, we don't
normally get a lot of
girls in here, you know?

07:45.382 --> 07:48.044
Listen, I'm just here
to deliver a message.

07:48.135 --> 07:49.295
(WHISPERING)
You're in danger.

07:49.386 --> 07:51.502
You need to get out
of here immediately.

07:52.723 --> 07:54.964
Victor.
What?

07:55.059 --> 07:57.766
Oh, come on, a hot blonde
in a comic book store? Please.

07:57.895 --> 08:01.058
Victor sent you, right?
This is payback for the whole
birthday thing, right?

08:01.190 --> 08:02.270
(WHISPERING)
Wait, let me guess.
Wait, wait.

08:02.399 --> 08:05.391
Is this all going to end
with you giving me, like,
a lap dance or something?

08:05.527 --> 08:10.396
No! You have to listen
to me, all right?
This is not a joke.

08:10.574 --> 08:12.405
There are people out there
who are after you.

08:12.534 --> 08:16.777
They will come in here
and take you away.
Yeah! In here?

08:17.373 --> 08:20.285
Oh, come on, you're gonna
have to do a betterjob
convincing me.

08:20.376 --> 08:21.786
(SIGHING)

08:32.471 --> 08:35.588
Your life is in danger.

08:37.226 --> 08:38.557
(DOOR OPENING)

08:44.358 --> 08:45.598
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

08:46.652 --> 08:48.267
Move. Now!

09:03.460 --> 09:05.291
Move. Now!

09:12.469 --> 09:14.881
(WHISPERING) You wanna
tell me what the hell
is going on?

09:14.972 --> 09:19.591
(WHISPERING) There's a man
in here, he's looking for you
and he's very, very dangerous.

09:19.727 --> 09:23.390
Do you have your car here?
Yeah, yeah,
but it's out back.

09:23.480 --> 09:25.266
Alex working today?

09:36.493 --> 09:41.328
Alex Woolsley.
I'm from the County
Clerk's office.

09:41.415 --> 09:46.000
I'm afraid we have a situation
with some outstanding parking
violations.

09:47.463 --> 09:49.749
Would you rather
just go talk outside?

09:49.840 --> 09:51.421
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

09:51.508 --> 09:52.714
Sorry.

09:54.052 --> 09:56.543
This isn't a really
good time.
Is it important?

09:56.805 --> 09:59.467
Look, Dad, ljust...
l was thinking about what
happened this morning

09:59.558 --> 10:01.389
and | just don't
want it to...

10:02.686 --> 10:05.223
Sweetheart, I'm gonna
have to call you back.

10:05.314 --> 10:06.554
(GROANING)

10:20.162 --> 10:21.493
Thatone.

10:23.707 --> 10:25.368
We're gonna need
a team down here.

10:26.376 --> 10:27.707
Come on,
come on,
come on.

10:31.590 --> 10:33.046
(TIRES SQUEALING)

10:39.056 --> 10:40.512
(HIRO SPEAKING JAPANESE)

10:53.237 --> 10:54.352
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

10:54.738 --> 10:57.024
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

11:09.545 --> 11:10.751
(SIGHING)

11:11.129 --> 11:13.745
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

11:18.428 --> 11:20.419
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

11:35.946 --> 11:37.402
Hello.

11:37.489 --> 11:39.980
Hi, my name is Ando.

11:40.117 --> 11:43.280
I'm sorry. Annapoora.
Annapoora.

11:44.079 --> 11:48.072
Your name is familiar.
Are you a guest
of the groom?

11:48.166 --> 11:49.827
(CHUCKLING)
No, not exactly.

11:50.836 --> 11:52.167
Are you okay?

11:52.462 --> 11:55.750
Just a little sad,
that's all.
On your wedding day?

11:56.425 --> 12:00.384
But this is supposed
to be the happiest day
of your life, isn't it?

12:00.470 --> 12:02.631
Yes, that's what they say.

12:06.101 --> 12:08.638
Then you must
call off the wedding.

12:14.484 --> 12:16.315
This is incredible.

12:17.195 --> 12:19.982
I've been feeling
so lost and confused.

12:21.199 --> 12:25.613
I've asked the heavens
for a sign telling me
whether I should marry or not.

12:25.704 --> 12:27.035
A sign...

12:28.707 --> 12:30.163
Yes, a sign.

12:34.922 --> 12:35.911
(EXHALES)

12:42.387 --> 12:43.968
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

12:44.598 --> 12:45.758
(EXCLAIMING HAPPILY)

12:45.849 --> 12:50.138
You are the sign.
You're the one
I've been waiting for.

12:50.479 --> 12:55.690
Sign? No, no, no!
It's not him, it's me.
I'm the sign.

12:56.526 --> 12:58.858
That's it.
The wedding is off!

13:05.535 --> 13:07.491
Do we have any response
from the White House?

13:07.663 --> 13:11.656
Nothing yet.
So these are the bad guys.

13:13.919 --> 13:16.285
Abby Collins.
Homeland Security.

13:16.380 --> 13:18.211
Nathan Petrelli.
Nice to meet you.

13:18.382 --> 13:22.000
The White House has
transferred oversight of
your operations to DHS.

13:22.094 --> 13:24.927
I'm here to kick
the tires and find out
what it is we bought.

13:25.097 --> 13:28.385
Just what we need,
another bureaucrat.

13:31.603 --> 13:33.559
Can I give you a tour?

13:34.606 --> 13:37.188
I don't know how
fully briefed you are on
what's happened here,

13:37.275 --> 13:38.651
but the last few days
have made it clear

13:38.735 --> 13:41.192
that Eagle Rock Prison
is woefully inadequate
for our needs.

13:41.279 --> 13:45.192
The reason I've asked for
such a large funding increase
is to reinforce the facility

13:45.283 --> 13:47.615
so I can deal with
these prisoners.

13:47.911 --> 13:50.402
Right, because
they're all magic.

13:56.128 --> 13:58.289
You don't believe
any of this, do you?

14:01.091 --> 14:03.207
Who put you on
this assignment, exactly?

14:03.301 --> 14:06.668
People close to the President
are concerned about
his exposure on this.

14:06.763 --> 14:09.254
Time travelers?
Mind readers?

14:15.647 --> 14:19.731
We are dealing with a threat
the likes of which this
country has never seen before.

14:19.818 --> 14:22.651
We need better containment.
I can barely handle
the one detainee...

14:22.779 --> 14:24.815
Are you telling me
that you're keeping
a prisoner here

14:24.948 --> 14:27.030
without warrant
or Miranda rights?

14:28.869 --> 14:32.487
I'm going to need to speak
with the President directly.

14:33.790 --> 14:36.452
Yeah, well, that's
not going to happen.

14:38.128 --> 14:41.666
I'm your new boss,
and I want to see
your prisoner now.

14:52.809 --> 14:55.141
This is what
I'm talking about.

14:55.312 --> 14:58.270
A place like this,
the worse the food,
the better.

14:58.356 --> 14:59.516
Luke.

15:00.484 --> 15:03.396
You really gotta stop trying
to be my friend or I'm going
to have to kill you.

15:03.487 --> 15:04.727
(CHUCKLES)

15:06.406 --> 15:08.146
Do you like birds?

15:13.497 --> 15:14.657
What?

15:15.707 --> 15:20.667
Well, no, I'm just wondering
if it's genetic because your
daddy is way into birding.

15:21.505 --> 15:25.544
I went with him sometimes.
He'd come get me up
about 4:00 am,

15:25.884 --> 15:28.500
and we'd be out
walking a trail by dawn.

15:29.387 --> 15:33.721
We'd see goldfinch,
cormorants, woodcocks.

15:34.184 --> 15:38.268
He would be
pulling this old,
rusty wagon behind him,

15:38.396 --> 15:42.014
carrying all
his bird books.
Red wagon.

15:42.109 --> 15:44.771
Yeah, it had these
big rubber wheels...

15:44.861 --> 15:47.443
He used to pull me
in that wagon.

15:51.034 --> 15:53.525
I remember laying
in a red wagon,

15:55.539 --> 15:57.655
all wrapped up
in blankets.

15:57.749 --> 16:01.708
It was still dark,
and the silhouettes
of the tree branches...

16:03.713 --> 16:06.375
I remember thinking
they looked like

16:08.260 --> 16:09.625
snake fingers.

16:11.888 --> 16:14.265
He sold you for money,
you know.

16:16.143 --> 16:19.476
He told me once
he had a little boy
a long time ago,

16:19.813 --> 16:23.055
but he needed cash,
so he sold him.

16:23.150 --> 16:25.732
What kind of man
sells his own son?

16:28.822 --> 16:31.985
Why would he even
tell you something
like that?

16:35.078 --> 16:37.319
Maybe I reminded him of you.

16:50.760 --> 16:53.968
Oh, my God.
I know. It looks harsh.

16:55.432 --> 16:58.344
We tried insulated gloves,
but she shattered
right through them.

16:59.644 --> 17:01.896
The constant heat
is to ensure...
Abby?

17:03.190 --> 17:05.101
This is Tracy Strauss.

17:05.859 --> 17:07.349
You know her?

17:07.861 --> 17:10.022
She used to lobby
for a defense contractor.

17:10.113 --> 17:12.354
Abby, they won't
let me out of here.
You have to do something.

17:12.449 --> 17:15.987
What is this insanity?
This woman is
extremely dangerous.

17:16.077 --> 17:17.487
Abby, he's lying.
You know me.

17:17.579 --> 17:21.071
This woman is Tracy Strauss,
and you have her shackled
to a chair.

17:21.208 --> 17:24.291
That's why we need
better funding.
Funding?

17:24.419 --> 17:29.504
I am shutting this operation
down today, and then
I'm going to the AG's office

17:29.591 --> 17:32.708
and I'm filing
human rights violations
against you, Senator.

17:32.886 --> 17:35.127
This is torture.
You're through.

17:35.722 --> 17:38.464
Abby? Abby!

17:58.662 --> 18:01.529
I can't believe it.
They're just
locking people up?

18:01.665 --> 18:03.496
BeHeveiL
it's happening.

18:03.583 --> 18:06.495
Somebody sent me
to warn you. You must be
on a list or something.

18:06.586 --> 18:09.293
List? Why is he after me?

18:11.132 --> 18:14.875
Do you have a power?
Like a special ability
or something?

18:19.182 --> 18:20.888
I can breathe underwater.

18:22.060 --> 18:24.676
You mean like...
Like a fish, yeah.

18:25.480 --> 18:27.596
I was on the swim team
in high school.

18:27.691 --> 18:31.855
One day, I noticed
ljust didn't have to
come up for air anymore.

18:32.988 --> 18:36.651
Never told anyone.
I didn't know
there were others.

18:38.201 --> 18:42.285
You'd think I'd be
proud of it or something,
but instead ljust...

18:44.874 --> 18:46.535
I feel like a...

18:47.627 --> 18:49.128
Like a freak?

18:51.214 --> 18:52.203
(CHUCKLES)

18:53.049 --> 18:56.132
Look, don't go home.
Don't use your credit cards
or your cell phone.

18:56.219 --> 18:58.926
If he can find you at work,
he can find you anywhere.

18:59.014 --> 19:01.096
So what am I going to do?

19:01.766 --> 19:04.633
I don't know.
We'll figure
something out.

19:12.861 --> 19:14.021
What?

19:14.112 --> 19:17.525
That car that drove past,
second time it went by.

19:18.742 --> 19:20.733
Is this car registered
under your name?

19:22.620 --> 19:23.905
Get out.

19:38.553 --> 19:39.542
Car's still warm.

19:41.056 --> 19:42.637
Believe me now?

19:43.516 --> 19:44.847
Let's go.

19:47.270 --> 19:52.390
The house specialties,
rasmalai, kheer,
halwa and jamun.

19:53.610 --> 19:57.569
ANDO: So this is your place?
With Shaila, yes.

19:58.615 --> 20:00.651
We opened two years ago.

20:01.159 --> 20:04.617
Against my
grandfather's wishes.
Your grandfather?

20:04.954 --> 20:06.160
He believes in tradition.

20:06.247 --> 20:08.954
Thinks women
should be at home,
raising the children.

20:09.042 --> 20:11.124
That's why he arranged
my marriage to Deepak.

20:11.211 --> 20:13.327
But you don't
love Deepak.

20:14.923 --> 20:18.256
He is a powerful
and dangerous man,
above the law.

20:20.095 --> 20:24.179
My grandfather was
too frightened to deny
his request to marry.

20:27.310 --> 20:30.723
You must be hungry, my hero.
Let me bring you more.

20:39.531 --> 20:41.692
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

20:41.950 --> 20:44.441
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

20:47.580 --> 20:49.992
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

20:50.959 --> 20:52.790
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

20:53.461 --> 20:55.998
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

20:58.633 --> 21:00.089
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

21:00.176 --> 21:02.963
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

21:13.523 --> 21:15.559
(SPEAKING HINDI)

21:22.532 --> 21:24.363
(DEEPAK SPEAKING HINDI)

21:25.201 --> 21:26.941
Deepak. The groom.

21:29.706 --> 21:30.946
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

21:35.003 --> 21:36.789
(SPEAKING HINDI)

21:36.880 --> 21:37.915
(SPEAKING HINDI)

21:38.006 --> 21:40.748
Excuse me!
Is everything
okay in here?

21:40.842 --> 21:44.334
Who the hell is this?
Ando. He is my friend.

21:44.471 --> 21:47.178
I see. So you canceled
the wedding because of him?

21:47.348 --> 21:49.555
Well, no, no, sir,
you're mistaken.
I am just a guest.

21:49.642 --> 21:50.973
Sir?
No!

21:51.060 --> 21:53.142
Calm down, sir. Sir!
No!

21:53.229 --> 21:54.218
(CRASHING)

21:54.314 --> 21:55.770
(ALL SHOUTING)

21:57.025 --> 21:58.185
Ando?

21:59.235 --> 22:02.227
Deepak hit him with this.
Ando collapsed.

22:03.031 --> 22:05.568
And then?
Deepak carried him off!

22:07.619 --> 22:08.779
Ando?

22:10.246 --> 22:13.283
We found his car.
He abandoned it
about half a mile away.

22:13.374 --> 22:15.990
For a local kid,
he's pretty good at this.

22:16.169 --> 22:18.831
If you're telling me
it doesn't smell right,
lnoﬂced.

22:20.465 --> 22:26.176
Do you know your daughter's
car is parked a half block
south of your location?

22:27.013 --> 22:28.514
Yeah, I saw that.

22:28.640 --> 22:31.552
She mentioned she had
some errands to run.

22:33.019 --> 22:34.634
It's a small town.

22:35.396 --> 22:36.806
We'll talk.

22:44.030 --> 22:45.315
(BLOWING BUBBLES)

22:50.119 --> 22:51.404
(SIGHS)

22:52.997 --> 22:54.498
At least tell me
how long this
is going to last.

22:54.582 --> 22:57.198
Are we driving
for another hour?
Another week?

22:57.293 --> 22:58.954
Hey, check out 22 Top.

23:03.925 --> 23:04.914
(EXCLAIMS)

23:05.009 --> 23:05.998
(GLASS SHATTERS)

23:06.094 --> 23:07.300
MAN: God!
Stop it!

23:07.387 --> 23:10.094
I'm just messing with him.
Not here.

23:11.140 --> 23:12.926
We don't need
the attention.

23:14.018 --> 23:17.681
Our powers are not
for amusement, Luke,
do you understand that?

23:17.897 --> 23:20.104
I don't know.
I've never really talked
to anyone about it before.

23:20.191 --> 23:23.103
My mom thinks
I'm enough of a freak as is.

23:24.320 --> 23:27.312
So, what?
You only use your
powers for a reason?

23:28.449 --> 23:31.316
Usually. Sometimes,
I disappoint myself.

23:36.207 --> 23:38.289
Always have an objective.

23:39.252 --> 23:42.210
Know your endgame
before you lift a hand.

23:43.172 --> 23:44.548
What else?

23:45.341 --> 23:48.333
Keep a clear head.
Emotions make you sloppy.

23:48.803 --> 23:53.217
The most important thing
is that you understand
your motivation.

23:53.308 --> 23:55.640
Always know what
it is that you want.

23:55.852 --> 23:57.934
What is it
that you want?

23:58.062 --> 23:59.393
For me, um...

24:00.940 --> 24:04.683
It's mostly been about
acquiring abilities.
But lately...

24:08.948 --> 24:11.815
Lately, all Iwant
to find is my father.

24:15.496 --> 24:18.078
I want to meet
the man who made me,

24:19.792 --> 24:21.657
look him in the eyes.

24:23.504 --> 24:26.120
What are you hoping
to see in there?

24:29.844 --> 24:32.005
Where I came from,
Iguess.

24:34.641 --> 24:37.007
Why I turned out
the way I did.

24:39.228 --> 24:42.812
I'm just thinking
he'll have some answers,
that's all.

24:46.277 --> 24:47.653
(SIGHING)

25:03.127 --> 25:06.085
This is the address.
It's a two-day drive.

25:09.008 --> 25:11.294
You shouldn't
have done that.

25:12.762 --> 25:15.299
Now there's nothing
to keep me from
killing you, is there?

25:15.431 --> 25:18.594
Well, I guess I'm just
hoping that you won't.

25:19.769 --> 25:21.134
(DOOR OPENING)

25:30.154 --> 25:32.987
Emergency exit.
Walk. Don't run.

25:33.616 --> 25:35.447
What?
Move.

25:40.206 --> 25:43.039
There's only two,
we can take them.
SYLAR: They're the scouts.

25:47.714 --> 25:48.703
(WOMEN SCREAMING)

25:48.798 --> 25:50.834
Got you.
Right on the sweet spot.

25:50.967 --> 25:53.174
Everyone on the floor.
Now!

25:59.892 --> 26:03.805
Please don't let him
hurt me anymore. Don't let
him hurt me anymore. Please!

26:03.896 --> 26:06.854
Please, just don't let
him hurt me anymore.
I want to go back to my mom.

26:06.983 --> 26:09.565
Please! ljust...
I want to go back...
Stand back!

26:09.652 --> 26:10.607
(SCREAMS)

26:10.695 --> 26:12.356
(PEOPLE SHOUTING)

26:32.049 --> 26:33.585
Hey, Sylar!

26:33.676 --> 26:35.507
Sylar!
Thanks for the address.

26:35.595 --> 26:36.675
What?

26:37.722 --> 26:39.678
Wait, Sylar.
Stop, stop.

26:39.766 --> 26:41.347
(TIRES SQUEALING)

26:42.059 --> 26:43.310
Sylar.

26:44.812 --> 26:46.393
(GUNSHOTS)

26:46.773 --> 26:48.980
AGENT: I'll follow him.
Stay on the kid.

26:53.571 --> 26:55.061
(FIRES)

27:06.709 --> 27:09.917
Deepak will let Ando go
if I honor my commitment
to marry.

27:10.046 --> 27:11.707
And if you don't?

27:14.926 --> 27:16.666
I must prepare
for the wedding.

27:18.179 --> 27:21.512
(CHANTING PRAYERS
IN SANSKRIT)

27:30.733 --> 27:33.725
Stop! This wedding
cannot go on.

27:34.237 --> 27:36.603
Annapoora cannot get
married to this man.

27:36.697 --> 27:39.279
She's being forced
into this against her will.

27:39.700 --> 27:41.236
You are making a mistake.

27:41.452 --> 27:44.569
You have kidnapped my friend.
I want him back!

27:45.540 --> 27:47.576
He's being held hostage.

27:47.875 --> 27:49.740
It is not I
who broke our agreement.

27:49.836 --> 27:51.701
She does not want
to marry you.

27:52.213 --> 27:55.922
(SPEAKING HINDI)

28:03.599 --> 28:07.091
All my life, I have tried
to please you, Grandfather.

28:07.603 --> 28:09.468
But if I marry Deepak,

28:10.439 --> 28:14.102
I will be giving up everything
that matters most to me.

28:18.072 --> 28:21.109
Perhaps a traditional marriage
is not my destiny.

28:23.160 --> 28:25.151
(SPEAKING HINDI)

28:25.288 --> 28:27.870
We had a deal.
The woman and the bakery
belong to me.

28:27.957 --> 28:28.946
(GROANING)

28:29.876 --> 28:31.457
(PEOPLE EXCLAIMING)

28:31.919 --> 28:33.705
You leave her alone.

28:33.796 --> 28:35.161
(PEOPLE EXCLAIMING)

28:37.508 --> 28:39.669
Give me back my friend.

28:42.805 --> 28:44.841
That's it!
The wedding is off!

28:45.182 --> 28:48.015
You're too much trouble,
I don't want to marry you.

28:48.144 --> 28:50.476
And you can have
your lousy friend back.

28:52.523 --> 28:55.481
This is it.
The moment in
the drawing.

28:55.860 --> 28:58.021
This is me,
being the hero!

28:58.988 --> 29:00.524
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

29:01.115 --> 29:02.730
(CAR BEEPING)

29:04.160 --> 29:07.197
So, how was your day?
Dad.

29:07.330 --> 29:08.820
You want to tell me
what the hell
you're doing here.

29:08.956 --> 29:11.242
I was just applying
for a job at
the coffee house.

29:11.334 --> 29:12.323
Stop it, Claire.

29:12.418 --> 29:14.079
What? They posted
a help wanted online.

29:14.170 --> 29:16.001
I know you're lying.

29:18.299 --> 29:20.836
Well, I did learn
from the master.

29:22.011 --> 29:25.048
You think
you're invincible,
but you're not.

29:25.473 --> 29:29.716
Just because you can't
be injured doesn't mean
you can't be caught.

29:29.852 --> 29:34.642
Do you have any idea
what happens if they think
I can't control you anymore?

29:35.274 --> 29:38.641
That's the thing,
Dad, you can't.

29:44.951 --> 29:46.487
(ENGINE STARTING)

29:49.956 --> 29:51.241
(SIGHING)

29:54.210 --> 29:57.293
Reports are in from the diner.
They brought down the kid,
Luke Campbell.

29:57.380 --> 29:58.540
Sylar?

30:01.884 --> 30:06.218
DHS is trying to take
us down, and all we have
is a 17-year-old boy.

30:07.390 --> 30:08.630
From the Office
of the Secretary.

30:08.724 --> 30:11.966
You are hereby notified
to cease and desist this
operation in its entirety.

30:12.061 --> 30:17.021
Abby, don't do this.
Give me five minutes.
Let me change your mind.

30:18.734 --> 30:23.068
Just suspend your disbelief
for a second and imagine
that these people exist,

30:23.155 --> 30:27.194
people who possess powers.
It still wouldn't
justify torture.

30:27.827 --> 30:29.442
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

30:32.039 --> 30:33.028
(GRUNTING)

30:38.421 --> 30:41.584
I'm talking about people
who could slice your head
open with their finger.

30:44.176 --> 30:46.918
Make you think what
they want you to think,
get inside your head.

30:47.096 --> 30:49.007
This is your argument?

30:49.223 --> 30:52.761
That these people are
so dangerous that they have
no constitutional rights?

30:55.312 --> 30:56.301
(GRUNTING)

31:02.445 --> 31:05.187
There is no justification
for treating people this way.

31:05.364 --> 31:06.865
And American citizens,
noless!

31:06.949 --> 31:11.534
You can't pull the plug
on a war when you haven't
even been to the front lines.

31:11.620 --> 31:12.826
(ALARM BEEPING)

31:12.913 --> 31:14.619
AGENT: Guards! Over here.
Excuse me.

31:20.796 --> 31:22.047
Tracy.

31:22.131 --> 31:23.871
(BEEPING STOPS)

31:31.599 --> 31:32.884
(SCREAMS)

31:33.309 --> 31:34.298
(GASPS)

31:39.648 --> 31:40.637
(GASPS)

31:42.318 --> 31:43.398
AGENT: Fire.

31:43.486 --> 31:44.475
(CRACKUNG)

32:14.600 --> 32:17.808
I'm really sorry
you had to witness
that today.

32:17.937 --> 32:20.178
I know how upsetting
that must have been.

32:20.314 --> 32:23.272
It's definitely something
I won't soon forget.

32:23.442 --> 32:26.354
I wouldn't be doing any
of this unless I believed
in the bottom of my heart

32:26.445 --> 32:28.686
that these people
are just too dangerous
to be among us.

32:28.823 --> 32:31.360
Don't worry. You'll have
all the funding you need.

32:38.707 --> 32:39.867
Don't fill up.

32:39.959 --> 32:43.042
Your dad's bringing home
takeout from that
new Indian place.

32:43.129 --> 32:44.539
Sounds good.

32:45.047 --> 32:46.878
I didn't mean
to pry this morning.

32:46.966 --> 32:51.050
Sounds like your trip
was a little... I don't know
what, disappointing?

32:52.638 --> 32:56.381
Did you guys have
any fun at all?
Take in a Broadway Show?

32:57.226 --> 32:59.137
Dad was a little busy.

33:02.314 --> 33:03.850
Abducting innocent people.

33:09.488 --> 33:14.323
He's not been
honest with you, Mom.
He's not a consultant.

33:14.577 --> 33:16.192
He's working for
a secret program,

33:16.287 --> 33:18.824
imprisoning people
with powers.

33:18.914 --> 33:20.415
The Company?

33:20.916 --> 33:25.034
No. No, the Company is gone.
This is something else.

33:26.755 --> 33:28.336
Honey, are you sure?
I mean, maybe he was...

33:28.424 --> 33:30.585
I was there. I saw it.

33:31.051 --> 33:33.508
They were loading prisoners
onto a transport plane.

33:33.596 --> 33:36.588
They had them all hooded,
they were drugged.

33:36.724 --> 33:38.385
It was horrible.

33:39.351 --> 33:40.761
Oh, my God.

33:41.353 --> 33:43.014
It's starting all over again.

33:43.105 --> 33:46.848
No, this is worse.
They're taking everyone.

33:46.942 --> 33:50.526
Not just dangerous people,
anyone with an ability.

33:51.030 --> 33:54.397
Matt Parkman,
Dr. Suresh, Peter...

33:59.288 --> 34:03.782
I'm sorry. ljust can't
lie to you anymore.

34:04.460 --> 34:05.745
(DOOR OPENING)

34:13.802 --> 34:15.258
Indian food?

34:17.890 --> 34:19.801
Go on upstairs, honey.

34:30.486 --> 34:32.147
MR. BENNET:
What's going on?

34:37.326 --> 34:40.739
Noah, I can't take it anymore,
ljust can't.
What are you talking about?

34:40.871 --> 34:42.486
I know what you're doing.
What's happened?

34:42.623 --> 34:44.454
Hunting people...
You don't know
what I've been doing.

34:44.541 --> 34:48.250
Don't lie to me, Noah.
You have no idea...

34:48.337 --> 34:50.703
I really wanted
to believe...
...how big this thing is.

34:50.798 --> 34:52.038
...that you could change.

34:52.132 --> 34:55.169
That you could be
someone different from
who you really are.

34:55.261 --> 34:58.219
Do you have any idea
how difficult this is?
Maybe I don't have a choice.

34:58.305 --> 35:00.136
There is always a choice!

35:00.224 --> 35:02.761
The government is putting
together a list of people
they are rounding up,

35:02.851 --> 35:04.637
and they have made it
very clear to me

35:04.728 --> 35:07.561
that if I am not on board,
that Claire will be
on that list!

35:07.648 --> 35:09.934
(SHOUTING) Don't make
this about Claire.

35:14.196 --> 35:15.697
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

35:23.622 --> 35:24.611
(DOOR CLOSING)

35:25.666 --> 35:28.248
(WHISPERING) Tracy,
I don't know
how you did it.

35:29.920 --> 35:31.421
But you'd better get
used to the heat

35:31.505 --> 35:33.621
because you are never
getting out of here again.

35:33.716 --> 35:35.502
We both know
what you did.

35:35.634 --> 35:39.422
What are you talking about?
Broken chain,
unlocked door...

35:41.765 --> 35:43.801
You wanted me to escape.

35:43.934 --> 35:48.268
You know what?
Next time I will.

35:56.196 --> 35:57.732
(CHATTER/NG ON POL/CE RAD/O)

36:02.619 --> 36:04.575
(BEEPING)

36:08.542 --> 36:10.498
(AGENTS SCREAMING)

36:10.878 --> 36:11.867
(AGENTS SCREAM/NG ON RAD/O)

36:11.962 --> 36:13.953
Hey, something's wrong.

36:14.173 --> 36:16.004
(THUDDING ON RAD/O)

36:16.091 --> 36:19.174
Team leader, this is...

36:19.261 --> 36:20.797
(BANG/NG ON RAD/O)

36:20.888 --> 36:23.971
Team leader,
this is Central.
Please respond.

36:26.477 --> 36:29.890
Team leader,
this is Central. Do you copy?
Repeat, Do you copy?

36:33.442 --> 36:36.525
This is Central Command.
Go to Channel B.
Please respond. Do you copy?

36:45.913 --> 36:48.996
Team leader,
this is Central.
Please respond.

36:59.343 --> 37:00.332
Hiro.

37:00.552 --> 37:02.167
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

37:05.724 --> 37:07.635
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

37:22.241 --> 37:24.857
I finally figured out
why your names
are so familiar.

37:24.952 --> 37:28.285
A fax came in addressed
to Hiro and Ando. See?

37:29.957 --> 37:32.289
It's from someone
named Rebel.

37:32.376 --> 37:35.118
Who?
Just an address
in Los Angeles

37:35.212 --> 37:38.579
and the words
"Save Matt Parkman."

37:41.218 --> 37:42.833
It's a message
from destiny.

37:50.936 --> 37:55.145
So you straightened it all
out with Mom, and now you're
off to a new assignment?

37:55.232 --> 37:56.312
No.

37:57.943 --> 38:01.151
No. Your mother wants me
to move out of the house
for a while.

38:03.657 --> 38:08.526
She's right.
We keep too many
secrets in this family.

38:12.332 --> 38:15.290
So I'm going to try
to be a better person,

38:16.336 --> 38:22.081
beﬂerhusband,
better father,
and not tell lies.

38:24.052 --> 38:26.634
And if we all work
really hard to be
honest with each other,

38:26.722 --> 38:32.558
then maybe we can heal
these wounds.

38:35.731 --> 38:37.517
But I'll be around.

38:39.902 --> 38:41.893
We'll get through this.

38:44.531 --> 38:46.567
I love you, Claire-bear.

39:05.928 --> 39:07.418
I'll see you.

39:52.307 --> 39:54.639
Thanks for coming
back for me.

39:54.935 --> 39:57.017
I didn't come back for you.
I came back for this.

39:57.145 --> 39:58.976
You just happened
to be there.
Mmm-hmm.

39:59.064 --> 40:02.147
They've tracked me twice
in less than a week.

40:02.317 --> 40:03.853
I knew if! kept driving,
it was only a matter of time

40:03.944 --> 40:07.562
before they caught up
to me again. I needed to
understand how they work.

40:07.656 --> 40:10.068
Still, you could
have just left me.

40:11.702 --> 40:13.283
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ON RAD/O)

40:14.496 --> 40:15.736
(SINGING) Psycho killer

40:17.624 --> 40:21.287
Fa-fa-far better...

40:28.510 --> 40:30.011
Mark Leggett.

40:31.972 --> 40:33.303
Excuse me?

40:33.390 --> 40:37.975
The analyst who died
in the hall today, that
was his name, Mark Leggett.

40:38.937 --> 40:41.223
I thought you'd want to know.

40:42.357 --> 40:45.895
He left a wife
and two kids.

40:49.990 --> 40:54.279
You let her out, didn't you?
You murdered an innocent man.

40:54.911 --> 40:59.871
There are times in a war
when someone has
to fall on a grenade.

41:00.125 --> 41:01.831
He didn't fail,
you threw him.

41:01.918 --> 41:03.624
I saved your ass.

41:04.338 --> 41:06.294
This entire project
was about to be flushed,

41:06.381 --> 41:08.872
and I helped us
both out, Petrelli.
It needed to be done.

41:10.677 --> 41:13.089
I'm sorry that
a man had to die.

41:13.680 --> 41:16.922
Why don't you go apologize
to his blood stain?
It's still warm.

41:31.239 --> 41:32.775
(SOFT ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

41:37.704 --> 41:39.820
Staying here
at the hotel?

41:43.251 --> 41:45.287
Just for a little while.

41:45.504 --> 41:49.998
I'm actually looking
for an apartment in town,
if you know of anything.

41:51.218 --> 41:52.458
Mmm-mmm.

41:53.345 --> 41:54.585
Welcome to Costa Verde.

41:54.680 --> 41:55.669
(SNICKERS)

42:05.190 --> 42:06.691
(MUS/C DISTORTED)

42:25.585 --> 42:28.076
Well, it looks like
our friend here had
about three too many.

42:28.171 --> 42:30.878
Don't worry.
We'll get him home safe.
